===Noun===
'''declension''' (''plural:'' [[declensions]])

#{{grammar}}: A way of categorizing of [[noun]]s, [[pronoun]]s, or [[adjective]]s according to the inflections they receive.
#: ''In Latin, 'amicus' belongs to the second declension. Most second-declension nouns end in 'i' in the genitive singular and 'um' in the accusative singular.''
#{{grammar}}: The act of [[declining]] a word; the act of listing the [[inflection]]s of a word in order.

